'''Konoe Nagako''' (近衛長子; 1218 – March 9, 1275) also known as '''Takatsukasa-in''' (鷹司院),<ref>''[https://books.google.com/books?id=c8rKCOSmKEMC&dq=Go-Horikawa+empress+%281218-1275%29&pg=PA309 The Clear Mirror: A Chronicle of the Japanese Court During the Kamakura]''</ref> was [[Empress of Japan]] as the consort of [[Emperor Go-Horikawa]].

==Notes==
{{reflist}}

{{s-start}}
{{s-roy|jp}}
{{succession box
| before = [[Fujiwara no Ariko]]
| title = [[Japanese empresses|Empress consort of Japan]]
| after = [[Kujō Shunshi]]
| years = 1226–1229
}}
{{s-end}}

